revision.text:
{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
The '''Binas''' (Often written as '''BiNaS''') is a Dutch science reference work for the higher levels of [[secondary school]], consisting largely of tables and formulas. The name stands for '''bi'''ologie, '''na'''tuurkunde, '''s'''cheikunde ([[biology]], [[physics]], [[chemistry]]). It is compiled by [[NVON]] and has been published by [[Noordhoff Uitgevers]] since 1975. There is also a smaller version for lower educational levels.

At most schools, students are allowed to use the BINAS for reference during a test or the final exam.

{{DEFAULTSORT:Binas}}
[[Category:Science books]]
[[Category:Dutch books]]


