{{Use Indian English|date=September 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox television | show_name = Guinness World Records – Ab India Todega | image = | caption = | genre = [[Reality television|Reality]] | creator = | developer = | writer = | director = | creative_director = | presenter = [[Preity Zinta]], [[Shabbir Ahluwalia]] | judges = | theme_music_composer = | opentheme = | endtheme = | composer = | country = [[India]] | language = [[English language|English]] | num_seasons = | num_episodes = | executive_producer = | producer = [[Niret Alva]] | editor = | location = | cinematography = | camera = [[Multi-camera]] | runtime = 60 minutes | company = | channel = [[Viacom 18|Colors TV]] | picture_format = [[720i]] ([[SDTV]]) | first_aired = {{start date|df=yes|2011|3|19}} | last_aired = {{end date|df=yes|2011|5|17}} | related = | website = http://www.colorstv.in/gwr/index.php}}
'''''Guinness World Records – Ab India Todega''''' (English: ''Guinness World Records – Now India will Break'') is a reality TV show based on the [[Guinness Book of World Records]]. The show, which was hosted by [[Preity Zinta]] and [[Shabbir Ahluwalia]], premiered on 18 March 2011 to an audience measurement of 3.3 rating points.<ref name="recordsn">{{cite web|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|author=Hegde, Rajul|title=Why Preity signed up for Guinness World Records|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-interview-with-preity-zinta/20110309.htm|date=2011-03-09|accessdate=2011-08-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=[[Hindustan Times]]|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Preity-scores-against-World-Cup-matches/Article1-677091.aspx|title=Preity scores against World Cup matches|date=2011-03-26|accessdate=2011-08-25|author=Dubey, Rechana}}</ref> Each episode presents different individuals trying to break official world records.<ref name="express">{{cite news|author=Aikara, Anita|title=Girl, interrupted|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/girl-interrupted/763879/0|date=2011-03-18|accessdate=2011-08-25|newspaper=[[The Indian Express]]}}</ref>
==Format== The format of the show is similar to that of previous TV shows based on the book of world records. The show's initial goal was to break over 70 Guinness World Records.<ref name="recordsn"/> [[Kristian Teufel]], an official Guinness World Records adjudicator, is present on stage while every participant attempts to break a record and constitutes the final authority on the record, being the one who analyses the performance and announces the results.<ref name="express"/>
==References== <references />
==External links== * [http://www.colorstv.in/gwr/index.php Official site] *[http://www.colorstv.in/shows/show-details/guinness-world-records-ab-india-todega-36/ Entry on Colors Channel] *[http://www.worldrecordsindia.com World Records Listing] {{Colors Programmes}}
